fluff

fluff is a utility to check trees of Perl source code for questionable
coding practices.  It is roughly analogous to the lint program for
checking C code.

INSTALLATION

To install this module, run the following commands:

    perl Makefile.PL
    make
    make test
    make install


SUPPORT AND DOCUMENTATION

After installing, you can find documentation for this module with the perldoc command.

    man fluff

You can also look for information at:

    Search CPAN
        http://search.cpan.org/dist/fluff

    CPAN Request Tracker:
        http://rt.cpan.org/NoAuth/Bugs.html?Dist=fluff

    AnnoCPAN, annotated CPAN documentation:
        http://annocpan.org/dist/fluff

    CPAN Ratings:
        http://cpanratings.perl.org/d/fluff

